<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3967.1.1>
    dc:creator "Huber, John T." ;
    dc:date "2015" ;
    dc:title "World reclassification of the Gonatocerus group of genera (Hymenoptera: Mymaridae)" ;
    bibo:endPage "184" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "1" ;
    bibo:volume "3967" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.288716>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.288751>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.288772>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.288773>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.288774>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.288775> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.288716>
    dc:description "FIGURES 6 – 9. Dorsal views: 6, Gonatocerus sp., entire body; 7, Lymaenon sp., entire body; 8, Lymaenon sp., pronotum, the lateral lobes widely separated medially; 9, Cosmocomoidea sp., pronotum, the lateral lobes abutting medially. Maximum diameter across mesoscutum (just anterior to fore wing base): 8 = 300 Μm, 9 = 330 Μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/288716/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.288751>
    dc:description "FIGURES 84 – 89. Gahanopsis deficiens, head: 84, anterior; 85, dorsal; 86, lateral; 87, posterior; 88, ventral; 89, mouthparts. Scale bars = 50 Μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/288751/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.288772>
    dc:description "FIGURES 175, 176. Lymaenon spp., habitus: 175, Central African Republic, Dzanga-Ndoki National Park, 2 ° 21.60 ' N 16 ° 03.20 ' E, 350 m, 23 – 24. v. 2001, S. van Noort, lowland rainforest (funicle 7 - segmented); 176, Malaysia, Sarawak, Gunung Buda, 4 ° 13 ' N 114 ° 56 ' E, 5. xi. 1996, S. L. Heydon & S. Fung (fl 6 and fl 7 white). Scale bars = 500 Μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/288772/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.288773>
    dc:description "FIGURES 177, 178. Lymaenon spp., habitus: 177, South Africa, West Cape, Kogelberg Nature Reserve, 3416.48 ' S 19 ° 01.03 ' E, 16. xi – 16. xii. 1998, S. van Noort, mesic mountain fynbos (ovipositor sheaths extending posteriorly well beyond gastral apex); 178, Australia, South Australia, 32 km N. Renmark, 263 m, 33 ° 53 ' S 140 ° 43 ' E, 15. ii – 15. iv. 2000, D. C. Darling (fore wing banded, ovipositor sheaths exserted anteriorly to head). Scale bars = 500 Μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/288773/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.288774>
    dc:description "FIGURES 179 – 184. Lymaenon sp., head: 179, anterior; 178, dorsal; 181, lateral; 182, posterior; 183, ventral; 184, mouthparts, ventral. Scale bars = 50 Μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/288774/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.288775>
    dc:description "FIGURES 185 – 190. Lymaenon sp.: 185, mesosoma dorsal; 186, mesosoma lateral; 187, mesosoma ventral; 188, mesosoma ventroanterior; 189, metasoma dorsal; 190, metasoma lateral. Scale bars = 50 Μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/288775/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

